---
// /changelog — public release notes. Stub for now; populates as we ship.
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Changelog — Echo-Synch"
  description="What's new in Echo-Synch — release notes for every shipped change."
>
  <header class="mk-pageheader">
    <div class="mk-container-narrow">
      <p class="mk-eyebrow">Changelog</p>
      <h1 class="mk-display">What's new</h1>
      <p class="mk-lead">
        Every shipped change, in reverse chronological order.
      </p>
    </div>
  </header>
  <article class="mk-prose">
    <p>Public release notes will land here as we ship. In the meantime, you can install Echo-Synch in your workspace at <a href="https://api.echo-synch.com/slack/install">api.echo-synch.com/slack/install</a> — every workspace gets a 14-day Enterprise trial, no credit card required.</p>
    <p>Questions? <a href="mailto:hello@echo-synch.com">hello@echo-synch.com</a></p>
  </article>
</Layout>
